@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home page";
}
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <title>Sustainability Indicator Classifiers for Moda Sostenible Barcelona</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f4f8; 
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: auto;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            padding: 20px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 2.5em;
        }

        section {
            background-color: white;
            padding: 40px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        section h2 {
            font-size: 1.8em;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            color: #333;
        }

        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        li {
            font-size: 1.2em;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #7f8c8d;
        }

        footer {
            background-color: #333;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>The Association</h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <p>We are a group of fashion designers, raw material suppliers, garment workshops, distributors, stores, journalists and citizens who have come together to demonstrate that the fashion industry does not have to be at odds with human rights and the environment.</p>
        <p>In 2013 we created the non-profit association Moda Sostenible Barcelona with the aim of raising awareness of the advantages of sustainable fashion as well as promoting and stimulating its creation, production, sale and use.</p>
        <p>We want the fashion industry to be more socially and environmentally responsible. We want to give strength to sustainable fashion designers and initiatives that promote another way of making and consuming fashion. We want society to discover that it is possible to dress well without exploiting people or harming the planet.</p>
    </section>

</body>
</html>